            The balance, if it is a balance, is one not only of a point of view, but also numerically of the number of people who hold either view&#x2014;it can only be that. What the noble Baroness is trying to balance, which simply does not work, is that the vast majority of people&#x2014;Roman Catholic, Protestant, ethnic minorities and those of no religion as we seem to include in some of the balances in Northern Ireland&#x2014;have no objection to the present court system.</p><p>
